<figcaption data-index="854"><p data-index="855"><span class="figureLabel" data-index="856"><b data-index="857"><a role="doc-backlink" href="#c10-fig-0004-1" data-index="858" data-section-index="20" data-section-idref="c10-fig-0004-1" data-target-data-index="769"><span style=" background-color: #127987; color: #FFFFFF;" data-index="859">ILLUSTRATION 10.4</span></a></b> <b data-index="860">Computation of Weighted-­Average Accumulated ­Expenditures</b></span></p></figcaption>
</figure>
<p data-index="861">Note that the expenditure made on December 31, the last day of the year, does not have any interest cost.</p>
<p data-index="862">Shalla computes the avoidable interest as shown in <a class="blue" id="c10-fig-0005-1" href="#c10-fig-0005" data-index="863" data-section-index="20" data-section-idref="c10-fig-0005" data-target-data-index="865"><b data-index="864">Illustration 10.5</b></a>.</p>
