</tr>
<tr data-index="1140">
<td data-index="1141">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cash ($112,500 + $55,000 + $72,000)</td>
<td data-index="1142"></td>
<td data-index="1143"><div class="right" data-index="1144">239,500</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p data-index="1145"><span epub:type="pagebreak" role="doc-pagebreak" title="10-11" id="Page_10-11" data-index="1146"></span>Shalla should write off capitalized interest cost as part of depreciation over the useful life of the assets involved and not over the term of the debt. It should disclose the total interest cost incurred during the period, with the portion charged to expense and the portion capitalized indicated.</p>
<p data-index="1147">At December 31, 2020, Shalla discloses the amount of interest capitalized either as part of the nonoperating section of the income statement or in the notes accompanying the financial statements. We illustrate both forms of disclosure, in <a class="blue" id="c10-fig-0007-1" href="#c10-fig-0007" data-index="1148" data-section-index="20" data-section-idref="c10-fig-0007" data-target-data-index="1154"><b data-index="1149">Illustration 10.7</b></a> and <a class="blue" id="c10-fig-0008-1" href="#c10-fig-0008" data-index="1150" data-section-index="20" data-section-idref="c10-fig-0008" data-target-data-index="1211"><b data-index="1151">Illustration 10.8</b></a>.<sup data-index="1152"><a id="c10-note-0004-1" href="#c10-note-0004" data-index="1153" data-section-index="20" data-section-idref="c10-note-0004" data-target-data-index="6615">4</a></sup></p>
<figure id="c10-fig-0007" data-index="1154">
