<h4 data-index="3737"><span class="red" data-index="3738">Instructions</span></h4>
<p data-index="3739">Compute the total cost for each of these two pieces of equipment. If an item is not capitalized as a cost of the equipment, indicate how it should be reported.</p>
<p data-index="3740"><span epub:type="pagebreak" role="doc-pagebreak" title="10-35" id="Page_10-35" data-index="3741"></span><b data-index="3742"><span class="codeColorBlue2" data-index="3743">E10.5</span></b> <span class="red" data-index="3744">(LO <a href="#h3_0003" data-index="3745" data-section-index="20" data-section-idref="h3_0003" data-target-data-index="216">1</a>, <a href="#h3_00010" data-index="3746" data-section-index="20" data-section-idref="h3_00010" data-target-data-index="396">2</a>)</span> <b data-index="3747">(Treatment of Various Costs)</b> Ben Sisko Supply Company, a newly formed corporation, incurred the following expenditures related to Land, to Buildings, and to Machinery and Equipment.</p>

