<p class="latin1" data-index="3988"><span class="label" data-index="3989"><b data-index="3990">a.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Assume that Harrisburg completed the office and warehouse building on December 31, 2020, as planned at a total cost of $5,200,000, and the weighted-average amount of accumulated expenditures was $3,600,000. Compute the avoidable interest on this project.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="3991"><span class="label" data-index="3992"><b data-index="3993">b.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Compute the depreciation expense for the year ended December 31, 2021. Harrisburg elected to depreciate the building on a straight-line basis and determined that the asset has a useful life of 30&nbsp;years and a salvage value of $300,000.</p>
