<h4 data-index="4426"><span class="red" data-index="4427">Instructions</span></h4>
<p data-index="4428">Record the acquisition of each of these assets.</p>
<p data-index="4429"><b data-index="4430"><span class="codeColorBlue2" data-index="4431">E10.17</span></b> <span class="red" data-index="4432">(LO <a href="#h3_00022" data-index="4433" data-section-index="20" data-section-idref="h3_00022" data-target-data-index="1296">3</a>)</span> <b data-index="4434">(Nonmonetary Exchange)</b> Busytown Corporation, which manufactures shoes, hired a recent college graduate to work in its accounting department. On the first day of work, the accountant was assigned to total a batch of invoices with the use of an adding machine. Before long, the accountant, who had never before seen such a machine, managed to break the machine. Busytown Corporation gave the machine plus $340 to Dick Tracy Business Machine Company (dealer) in exchange for a new machine. Assume the following information about the machines.</p>
